cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on place recognition using image descriptors and GNSS data. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper proposes an algorithm for a wearable assistive device for visually impaired people. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper mentions assigning different weights to descriptors in image matching. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes an algorithm for solving a challenging issue in assistive technology. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper focuses on developing an algorithm for visually impaired people.
